main event: Multiple eyewitnesses reported observing a white circular object over Lockbourne Air Force Base in Licking County, Ohio, on September 28, 1965.
interesting points: The object was first observed appearing as a bright star before intensifying in brightness,It was reported to have no tail and gradually faded out after a few minutes of observation,The object was estimated to be flying at altitudes between 15,000 and 70,000 feet,Several official reports documented the sightings from different observers including a deputy sheriff and Air Force personnel,The sightings were later investigated but resulted in negative radar identification.
witness description: Deputy Sheriff and Air Force personnel
